      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPENCER BANNER (1) goes very well this course and distance starting six times for two wins and two minors. Was out of the placings last time (30.17) at this track in a NG, finishing eighth and beaten 6 lengths. Looks the one to beat with even luck. SPRING WITNESS (2) turned in a moderate run last time when fifth at this track over 520m behind Raymar Shame (30.15) in a Grade 4/5. Should be in this for a long way. BLUE STORM (8) has a strong record this trip with four wins and two placings from nine starts. Below best last time at this track (30.28) in a NG, finishing a 14 length sixth. Looks suited here and can measure up. TEXAS BANDIT (5) returns from a six weeks layoff in a suitable contest.",
